<subSubSection id="C3136AEB574EFFAAFF585BDBFDF020BF" pageId="9" pageNumber="440" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB63960574EFFAAFF585BDBFDF020BF" blockId="9.[151,1437,295,502]" pageId="9" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis id="B97DE572574EFFAAFF585BDBFEF920E4" bold="true" box="[199,334,403,429]" pageId="9" pageNumber="440">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name honors the Brazilian arachnologist Nancy Lo-Man-Hung, who encouraged the first author to study spiders and contributed in academics by her persistence at fighting for woman rights in the Support Woman in Arachnology (SWA) group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF7669E8574EFFAAFF085D14FE4F26A9" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417678" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6417678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417678/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="440" startId="9.[151,264,1884,1908]" targetBox="[176,1417,535,1861]" targetPageId="9">
