<subSubSection id="C3136AEB574DFFA9FF585ADEFD0E2054" pageId="10" pageNumber="441" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB63960574DFFA9FF585ADEFD0E2054" blockId="10.[151,1437,150,1221]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">
<emphasis id="B97DE572574DFFA9FF585ADEFEF521F9" bold="true" box="[199,322,150,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E3574DFFA9FE305ADFFD3621F9" authorityName="Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues" authorityYear="2022" box="[431,641,151,177]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Guriurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nancyae">
<emphasis id="B97DE572574DFFA9FE305ADFFD3621F9" box="[431,641,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Guriurius nancyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by the rounded lower edge of the RvTA (
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FA885ADFFA2021F8" box="[1303,1431,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–26" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1151,1175]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,181,1124]" captionTargetId="figure-22@8.[158,1430,181,1128]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 21–26. Genitalic ilustration of Guriurius Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues gen. nov. Left male palp Guriurius minuano Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. (MCN 32225): 21 ventral view, white arrow: RvTA angular axis; 22 retrolateral view, scale bars: 0.25 mm. Epigyne of G. minuano (MCTP 40587): 23 ventral view; 24 dorsal view, white arrow: dorsally chitinized plate, scale bars: 0.10 mm. Left male palp of Guriurius nancyae Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. (MCN 30545): 25 ventral view, white arrow: RvTA rounded axis; 26 retrolateral view, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417670" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417670/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">
Figs 25 
<emphasis id="B97DE572574DFFA9FAF45ADFFACE21F8" bold="true" box="[1387,1401,151,177]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">–</emphasis>
26
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FF085AF3FF04219C" box="[151,179,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–34" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[176,1417,535,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-112@9.[158,1430,525,1861]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27–34. Male of Guriurius nancyae Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. Habitus (MCTP 30545): 27 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 28 ventral view; 29 lateral view; 30 face, frontal view, scale bars: 0.50 mm. Left male palp: 31 ventral, white arrow: RvTA rounded axis; 32 dorsal; 33 prolateral 34 retrolateral view, arrow: RvTA rounded axis, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417678/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">31</figureCitation>
<emphasis id="B97DE572574DFFA9FF2C5AF2FF0B219D" bold="true" box="[179,188,186,212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">)</emphasis>
and the hooked-shaped RvTA, curved upwards (anterior portion of tegulum), with a rounded distal axis (
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FAF55AF3FF6821B0" captionStart="FIGURES 21–26" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1151,1175]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,181,1124]" captionTargetId="figure-22@8.[158,1430,181,1128]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 21–26. Genitalic ilustration of Guriurius Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues gen. nov. Left male palp Guriurius minuano Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. (MCN 32225): 21 ventral view, white arrow: RvTA angular axis; 22 retrolateral view, scale bars: 0.25 mm. Epigyne of G. minuano (MCTP 40587): 23 ventral view; 24 dorsal view, white arrow: dorsally chitinized plate, scale bars: 0.10 mm. Left male palp of Guriurius nancyae Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. (MCN 30545): 25 ventral view, white arrow: RvTA rounded axis; 26 retrolateral view, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417670" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417670/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">
Figs 25 
<emphasis id="B97DE572574DFFA9FF2C5A97FF7621B0" bold="true" box="[179,193,223,249]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">–</emphasis>
26
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FF745A97FE8221B0" box="[235,309,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–34" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[176,1417,535,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-112@9.[158,1430,525,1861]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27–34. Male of Guriurius nancyae Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. Habitus (MCTP 30545): 27 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 28 ventral view; 29 lateral view; 30 face, frontal view, scale bars: 0.50 mm. Left male palp: 31 ventral, white arrow: RvTA rounded axis; 32 dorsal; 33 prolateral 34 retrolateral view, arrow: RvTA rounded axis, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417678/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">31, 34</figureCitation>
). Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E3574DFFA9FE2D5A97FD8521B1" authorityName="Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues" authorityYear="2022" box="[434,562,223,249]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Guriurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nancyae">
<emphasis id="B97DE572574DFFA9FE2D5A97FD8521B1" box="[434,562,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">G. nancyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E3574DFFA9FC995A97FC3D21B1" authorityName="Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues" authorityYear="2022" box="[774,906,223,249]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Guriurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuano">
<emphasis id="B97DE572574DFFA9FC995A97FC3D21B1" box="[774,906,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">G. minuano</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the circular-shape of the tegulum, but differ by the angulation axis more oblique (
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FDA75B4BFD362054" box="[568,641,258,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1871,1895]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,462,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-160@5.[151,1435,453,1848]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Male of Guriurius minuano Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. Habitus (MCTP 21675): 1 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern, 2 ventral view; 3 lateral view; 4 face, frontal view; scale bars: 1.00 mm. Left male palp (MCN 32225): 5 ventral view, white arrow: RvTA angular axis; 6 dorsal view; 7 prolateral view; 8 retrolateral view, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417650" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417650/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Figs 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FD125B4BFD1B2054" box="[653,684,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–34" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[176,1417,535,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-112@9.[158,1430,525,1861]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27–34. Male of Guriurius nancyae Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. Habitus (MCTP 30545): 27 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 28 ventral view; 29 lateral view; 30 face, frontal view, scale bars: 0.50 mm. Left male palp: 31 ventral, white arrow: RvTA rounded axis; 32 dorsal; 33 prolateral 34 retrolateral view, arrow: RvTA rounded axis, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417678/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">31</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3136AEB574DFFA9FF585B6EFE152534" pageId="10" pageNumber="441" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB63960574DFFA9FF585B6EFE142510" blockId="10.[151,1437,150,1221]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">
<emphasis id="B97DE572574DFFA9FF585B6EFEEE2009" bold="true" box="[199,345,294,320]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B97DE572574DFFA9FEFC5B6FFE2A2008" box="[355,413,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="54B287C2574DFFA9FE315B6FFDAF2008" box="[430,536,295,321]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Holotype</typeStatus>
MCTP 30545). Length: 3.30. Carapace length: 1.74 width, 1.53 height: 0.81. Cephalic region length: 1.56. Thoracic region length: 0.26. Ocular area length: 1.02; Anterior eyes row: 1.09 wide; Posterior eyes row: 1.17 wide; Distances ALE–PME: 0.13; PME–PLE: 0.26; Ocular diameter AME: 0.42; ALE: 0.18; PME: 0.06; PLE: 0.12. Clypeus height: 0.08. Chelicerae, paturon length: 0.46; 0.23 wide; Fang: 0.23 length. Endites length: 0.35; 0.31 wide. Labium length: 0.10; 0.21 wide. Sternum length: 0.65; 0.46 wide. Abdomen length: 1.58; 1.06 wide; height: 0.74. Legs: femur length I: 0.85; II: 0.68; III: 0.68; IV: 1.02; patella I: 0.68; II: 0.51; III: 0.40; IV: 0.51; tibia I: 1.02; II: 0.68; III: 0.51; IV: 0.68; metatarsus I: 0.68; II: 0.44; III: 0.51; IV: 0.68; tarsus I: 0.34; II: 0.34; III: 0.34; IV: 0.51. Formula legs: 1423. Palp, femur length: 0.46, patella: 0.21, tibia: 0.10, cymbium: 0.46. Palp macrosetae, femur d1. Legs macrosetae, femur I: d1-1-1, p1di; II: d1-1-1, p1di, r1di; III: d0-1-1, p0-0-2, r1di; IV: d1-1-1, p0-0-2, r1di, patella I–II: p0-1-0; III–IV: 0, tibia I: p1di, r0-1-1, v0; II: p1di, r0-1-1, v0; III: p0-1-1, r1di, v1di; IV: p1-1-1, r0-1-1, v2di, metatarsus I: d2di, p2di, r2di, v2di; II: v0-2-2; III: v2di, r2di, p2di; IV: v2di, r0-1-2, p0-1-2. Carapace as described for the genus (
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FD0E58FBFC892384" box="[657,830,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–34" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[176,1417,535,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-112@9.[158,1430,525,1861]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27–34. Male of Guriurius nancyae Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. Habitus (MCTP 30545): 27 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 28 ventral view; 29 lateral view; 30 face, frontal view, scale bars: 0.50 mm. Left male palp: 31 ventral, white arrow: RvTA rounded axis; 32 dorsal; 33 prolateral 34 retrolateral view, arrow: RvTA rounded axis, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417678/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Figs 27, 29, 30</figureCitation>
). Eyes as described for genus. Clypeus dark (
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FAA458FBFA382384" box="[1339,1423,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–34" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[176,1417,535,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-112@9.[158,1430,525,1861]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27–34. Male of Guriurius nancyae Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. Habitus (MCTP 30545): 27 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 28 ventral view; 29 lateral view; 30 face, frontal view, scale bars: 0.50 mm. Left male palp: 31 ventral, white arrow: RvTA rounded axis; 32 dorsal; 33 prolateral 34 retrolateral view, arrow: RvTA rounded axis, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417678/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
), with white scales. Chelicerae as in genus. Endites brown with apex lighter, anterior margin slightly more robust, without protruding external angles (
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FDB258B3FD35225C" box="[557,642,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–34" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[176,1417,535,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-112@9.[158,1430,525,1861]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27–34. Male of Guriurius nancyae Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. Habitus (MCTP 30545): 27 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 28 ventral view; 29 lateral view; 30 face, frontal view, scale bars: 0.50 mm. Left male palp: 31 ventral, white arrow: RvTA rounded axis; 32 dorsal; 33 prolateral 34 retrolateral view, arrow: RvTA rounded axis, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417678/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). Labium dark, wider than long and lighter at apex (
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FB4B58B3FA9E225C" box="[1236,1321,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–34" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[176,1417,535,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-112@9.[158,1430,525,1861]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27–34. Male of Guriurius nancyae Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. Habitus (MCTP 30545): 27 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 28 ventral view; 29 lateral view; 30 face, frontal view, scale bars: 0.50 mm. Left male palp: 31 ventral, white arrow: RvTA rounded axis; 32 dorsal; 33 prolateral 34 retrolateral view, arrow: RvTA rounded axis, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417678/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). Sternum brown, apex slightly narrower than the base of the labium, brown, longer than wide and inverted pentagonal shape (
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FF3F590BFF432214" box="[160,244,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–34" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[176,1417,535,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-112@9.[158,1430,525,1861]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27–34. Male of Guriurius nancyae Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. Habitus (MCTP 30545): 27 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 28 ventral view; 29 lateral view; 30 face, frontal view, scale bars: 0.50 mm. Left male palp: 31 ventral, white arrow: RvTA rounded axis; 32 dorsal; 33 prolateral 34 retrolateral view, arrow: RvTA rounded axis, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417678/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). Legs coloration as described for the genus. Male palp: femur yellow. Tibia with RTA without lobes, large base and sinuous tip (in lateral view), sclerotinized, conspicuous, half the size of the tegulum (
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FB5D592FFAAE22C8" box="[1218,1305,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–26" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1151,1175]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,181,1124]" captionTargetId="figure-22@8.[158,1430,181,1128]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 21–26. Genitalic ilustration of Guriurius Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues gen. nov. Left male palp Guriurius minuano Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. (MCN 32225): 21 ventral view, white arrow: RvTA angular axis; 22 retrolateral view, scale bars: 0.25 mm. Epigyne of G. minuano (MCTP 40587): 23 ventral view; 24 dorsal view, white arrow: dorsally chitinized plate, scale bars: 0.10 mm. Left male palp of Guriurius nancyae Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. (MCN 30545): 25 ventral view, white arrow: RvTA rounded axis; 26 retrolateral view, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417670" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417670/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Figs 26</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FAB9592FFAF122C8" box="[1318,1350,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–34" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[176,1417,535,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-112@9.[158,1430,525,1861]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27–34. Male of Guriurius nancyae Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. Habitus (MCTP 30545): 27 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 28 ventral view; 29 lateral view; 30 face, frontal view, scale bars: 0.50 mm. Left male palp: 31 ventral, white arrow: RvTA rounded axis; 32 dorsal; 33 prolateral 34 retrolateral view, arrow: RvTA rounded axis, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417678/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">34</figureCitation>
). RvTA inserted ventrally, below the tegulum, with retrolateral inclination, with a few scales on the dorsum, hooked-shaped, rounded axis, curved distal part of the tegulum (
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FD2359E7FC892280" box="[700,830,942,969]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–26" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1151,1175]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,181,1124]" captionTargetId="figure-22@8.[158,1430,181,1128]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 21–26. Genitalic ilustration of Guriurius Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues gen. nov. Left male palp Guriurius minuano Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. (MCN 32225): 21 ventral view, white arrow: RvTA angular axis; 22 retrolateral view, scale bars: 0.25 mm. Epigyne of G. minuano (MCTP 40587): 23 ventral view; 24 dorsal view, white arrow: dorsally chitinized plate, scale bars: 0.10 mm. Left male palp of Guriurius nancyae Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. (MCN 30545): 25 ventral view, white arrow: RvTA rounded axis; 26 retrolateral view, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417670" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417670/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">
Figs 25 
<emphasis id="B97DE572574DFFA9FC8D59E7FC972280" bold="true" box="[786,800,943,969]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">–</emphasis>
26
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FCD459E7FC762280" box="[843,961,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–34" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[176,1417,535,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-112@9.[158,1430,525,1861]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27–34. Male of Guriurius nancyae Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. Habitus (MCTP 30545): 27 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 28 ventral view; 29 lateral view; 30 face, frontal view, scale bars: 0.50 mm. Left male palp: 31 ventral, white arrow: RvTA rounded axis; 32 dorsal; 33 prolateral 34 retrolateral view, arrow: RvTA rounded axis, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417678/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">
31, 33 
<emphasis id="B97DE572574DFFA9FC0C59E7FC162280" bold="true" box="[915,929,943,969]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">–</emphasis>
34
</figureCitation>
). Cymbium suboval, with a rounded apex with a tuft of yellow setae, a lighter distal region, and brown proximal region (
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FB92599BFBD622A4" box="[1037,1121,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–34" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[176,1417,535,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-112@9.[158,1430,525,1861]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27–34. Male of Guriurius nancyae Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. Habitus (MCTP 30545): 27 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 28 ventral view; 29 lateral view; 30 face, frontal view, scale bars: 0.50 mm. Left male palp: 31 ventral, white arrow: RvTA rounded axis; 32 dorsal; 33 prolateral 34 retrolateral view, arrow: RvTA rounded axis, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417678/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
). Tegulum circular, inclined obliquely in relation to the apex of the cymbium (
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FD7A59BFFC8B2558" box="[741,828,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–34" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[176,1417,535,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-112@9.[158,1430,525,1861]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27–34. Male of Guriurius nancyae Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. Habitus (MCTP 30545): 27 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 28 ventral view; 29 lateral view; 30 face, frontal view, scale bars: 0.50 mm. Left male palp: 31 ventral, white arrow: RvTA rounded axis; 32 dorsal; 33 prolateral 34 retrolateral view, arrow: RvTA rounded axis, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417678/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
). Embolus slender, ribbon-like, embolar base dorsoprolateral (07:00 o’clock), embolar path around the tegulum (150º) (
<figureCitation id="133225E5574DFFA9FC2A5E53FB89257C" box="[949,1086,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–34" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[176,1417,535,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-112@9.[158,1430,525,1861]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27–34. Male of Guriurius nancyae Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues sp. nov. Habitus (MCTP 30545): 27 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 28 ventral view; 29 lateral view; 30 face, frontal view, scale bars: 0.50 mm. Left male palp: 31 ventral, white arrow: RvTA rounded axis; 32 dorsal; 33 prolateral 34 retrolateral view, arrow: RvTA rounded axis, scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417678" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417678/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Figs 31, 33</figureCitation>
). Abdomen and spinnerets: as described for the genus.
</paragraph>
